s. All the CSS is generated and applied under the hood, making it possible to make dramatic changes without knowing coding at all.</p>\\n\\n<h2 id=\\"item-description__tech-details\\">Tech details</h2>\\n<ul>\\n<li><strong>100% compatible</strong> with any theme that can load JS correctly, any plugins including Visual Composer, WooCommerce, sliders, BuddyPress, Layers, etc. Can tweak any HTML element</li>\\n<li><strong>Can tweak any elements</strong> as long as the tweaks are possible with CSS.</li>\\n<li>Saves tweaks to the database as ready-to-use CSS code you can copy and edit. Other plugin or theme files are not touched, so you can safely upgrade them later.</li>\\n</ul>\\n\\n<p><img src=\\"http://cdn.karevn.com/envato/stylez/poster-skyscraper.png\\" /></p>\\n\\n<h2 id=\\"item-description__testimonials\\">Testimonials</h2>\\n<p><img src=\\"//cdn.karevn.com/envato/stylez/testimonials.png\\" /></p>\\n\\n<h2 id=\\"item-description__installation-and-usage\\">Installation and usage</h2>\\nInstallation, <strong>recommended</strong> way:\\n<ol>\\n    <li>Download a plugin file from CodeCanyon.</li>\\n    <li>Log into your WordPress admin area.</li>\\n    <li>Go to &#8220;Plugins&#8221;, click &#8220;Add new&#8221; link at the top.</li>\\n    <li>Click &#8220;upload&#8221;, choose a file downloaded in the file selector field and submit the form.</li>\\n    <li>Click &#8220;Activate&#8221; next to STYLEZ.</li>\\n    <li>\\n        STYLEZ plugin&#8217;s interface will be available to admins (only) \\n        at your site frontend.\\n    </li>\\n</ol>\\n\\nInstallation, second way:\\n<ol>\\n    <li>Download a plugin file from CodeCanyon.</li>\\n    <li>Unzip the plugin archive.</li>\\n    <li>Open FTP client of your choice, upload the folder unzipped to your WordPress\\n        installation&#8217;s wp-content/plugins folder. Make sure you did not add an extra\\n        folder hierarchy and plugin .php files are right at \\n        <code>wp-content/plugins/stylez</code> fol